\viewkind4\uc1\pard\li15\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw2\f0\fs16 If you suffer a \b capital  loss \b0 while the policy is in force and survive it for 30 days, we will pay the capital sum for each loss. But we will not pay for more than two such losses in your li
fetime.    \cf0\expndtw0\kerning2 
\par \cf1\expndtw2\kerning0 
\par A capital loss means the entire loss of the sight in one eye, with no possible recovery; or the complete loss of a hand or foot by severance through or above the wrist or ankle. Such loss must result from a sickness or injury. If your policy terminat
es, we will pay for a capital loss, which results from an i njury sustained while this policy was in force, and which occurs within 90 days after the date of that injury.    \cf0\expndtw0\kerning2 
\par \cf1\expndtw2\kerning0 
\par The capital sum benefit is \b 12 times the monthly indemnity\b0 , including any SIS. This is a lump sum benefit payable in addition to any other indemnity payable under the policy.    
